<p>Paste the codes below at the bottom of the html elements in the&nbsp;<span style="background-color: rgb(206, 212, 217);"><strong>index.html</strong></span> file</p>
<p><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong>&lt;/<span style="color: rgb(248, 202, 198);">body</span>&gt;</strong></span><br><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong>&lt;<span style="color: rgb(248, 202, 198);">script </span><span style="color: rgb(191, 237, 210);">type</span><span style="color: rgb(248, 202, 198);">=</span><span style="color: rgb(251, 238, 184);">"text/javascript"</span>&gt;</strong></span><br><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; xHttpOP <span style="color: rgb(248, 202, 198);">= new</span> <span style="color: rgb(236, 202, 250);">XMLHttpRequest</span>()</strong></span><br><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; xHttpOP.<span style="color: rgb(194, 224, 244);">onload </span>= <span style="color: rgb(194, 224, 244);">function</span>(){</strong></span><br><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <span style="color: rgb(194, 224, 244);">document</span>.<span style="color: rgb(191, 237, 210);">querySelector</span>(<span style="color: rgb(251, 238, 184);">'.profile'</span>).<span style="color: rgb(191, 237, 210);">innerHTML </span>= <span style="color: rgb(251, 238, 184);">this</span>.responseText;</strong></span><br><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; }</strong></span><br><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; xHttpOP.<span style="color: rgb(194, 224, 244);">open</span>(<span style="color: rgb(251, 238, 184);">'GET'</span>,<span style="color: rgb(251, 238, 184);">'profile.html'</span>);</strong></span><br><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; xHttpOP.<span style="color: rgb(194, 224, 244);">send();</span></strong></span><br><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong>&lt;/<span style="color: rgb(248, 202, 198);">script</span>&gt;</strong></span><br><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong>&lt;/<span style="color: rgb(248, 202, 198);">html</span>&gt;</strong></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">I will explain these lines to you if you are a beginner in <span style="color: rgb(230, 126, 35);"><strong>javascript</strong></span><br><span style="color: rgb(45, 194, 107);"><strong>Before I explain it to you::,</strong></span>&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">let me tell you how the content of an external file is displayed in the current file<br>We fetch html content from<strong> <span style="background-color: rgb(206, 212, 217);">profile.html</span> </strong>file and set this content in <span style="background-color: rgb(206, 212, 217);"><strong>index.html</strong></span> file using <strong><span style="background-color: rgb(236, 202, 250);">innerHTML</span> </strong>to display the requested web page</span><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong><br></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The <strong><span style="background-color: rgb(236, 202, 250);">XMLHttpRequest</span> </strong>object gives us the ability to send and receive data from a web server without reloading the page:<br>In this case, we can fetch data from another file (just as you fetched the content of the <span style="background-color: rgb(206, 212, 217);"><strong>profile.html</strong></span> file).<br></span></p>
<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">As for this line <span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><strong><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="color: rgb(236, 240, 241);">xHttpOP.open</span>(<span style="color: rgb(251, 238, 184);">'GET'</span>,<span style="color: rgb(251, 238, 184);">'profile.html'</span>);</span></strong></span> It specifies the request <strong>(meaning: the file or url from which data is requested)</strong><br>As for <strong><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="color: rgb(236, 240, 241);">xHttpOP</span>. <span style="color: rgb(194, 224, 244);">send()</span>;</span></strong> It sends the request to the <strong>server </strong>in order for the response to come<br></span></p>
<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The response comes using&nbsp;<span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> <span style="color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong>xHttpOP.<span style="color: rgb(194, 224, 244);">onload&nbsp;</span></strong></span></span><span style="color: rgb(194, 224, 244);"> </span>as described below</span></p>
<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong>xHttpOP.<span style="color: rgb(194, 224, 244);">onload </span>= <span style="color: rgb(191, 237, 210);">function</span>(){</strong></span><br><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong><span style="color: rgb(194, 224, 244);">document</span>.querySelector(<span style="color: rgb(251, 238, 184);">'.profile'</span>).<span style="color: rgb(194, 224, 244);">innerHTML </span>= <span style="color: rgb(241, 196, 15);">this</span>.responseText;</strong></span><br><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong>}</strong></span><br></span></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&lt; A function must be defined inside onload as above &gt;&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">where this <span style="color: rgb(53, 152, 219);"><strong>function </strong></span>defined in onload is called when the request is received thus we get the data in <strong>this.responseText</strong> and the content of the <span style="background-color: rgb(206, 212, 217);"><strong>profile.html</strong></span> file is included in the <span style="background-color: rgb(206, 212, 217);"><strong>index.html</strong></span> file by this line</span><br><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="color: rgb(236, 240, 241);"><strong><span style="color: rgb(194, 224, 244);">document</span>.<span style="color: rgb(191, 237, 210);">querySelector</span>(<span style="color: rgb(251, 238, 184);">'.profile'</span>).<span style="color: rgb(194, 224, 244);">innerHTML </span>= <span style="color: rgb(241, 196, 15);">this</span>.responseText;</strong></span></span></p>
<p><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Now we want to add a profile picture to our <span style="background-color: rgb(206, 212, 217);"><strong>profile.html</strong></span> file.
